whatly (6.5.0) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Automatic recovery from a start-up GPU/GL crash: fall back to safer
    software rendering and log Chromium's own output for bug reports (#3).
  * Settings reorganised into themed, collapsible sections (#9).
  * Emoji panel no longer closes when picking a skin tone (#6).
  * HD photos render as soon as linked devices receive them (#7).
  * Notification popup stays fully on-screen (#5); consistent download
    paths on every platform (#4); on Windows, a tray click hides a
    frontmost window again (#8). See CHANGELOG.md.

 -- Ángel Guzmán Maeso <angel@guzmanmaeso.com>  Fri, 24 Jul 2026 18:00:00 +0200

whatly (6.4.0) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Command palette (Ctrl+K) with fuzzy search over actions and accounts.
  * Do Not Disturb schedule and keyword highlights for notifications.
  * Recurring scheduled messages and reminder mode.
  * Update checker, storage manager and customisable keyboard shortcuts.
  * Profile backup/restore, lock when the screen locks.
  * Working screen sharing (picker + PipeWire), quick reply, focus mode,
    saved replies and grid tile captions. See CHANGELOG.md.

 -- Ángel Guzmán Maeso <angel@guzmanmaeso.com>  Mon, 20 Jul 2026 18:00:00 +0200

whatly (6.3.0) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Performance & Privacy settings: GPU, process-model, JS-heap and HTTP-cache
    controls, plus a WebRTC IP-leak shield.
  * Network proxy (System/None/SOCKS5/HTTP), start-at-login, interface scale,
    and an optional custom (frameless) window frame.
  * Portal-based notifications for Flatpak, selectable per delivery backend.
  * Custom JavaScript addons (sandboxed); custom CSS and addons stored per
    account.
  * Grid view for multiple in-window accounts, alongside tabs and windows.
  * First-run setup wizard, and an optional custom window frame. See CHANGELOG.md.

 -- Ángel Guzmán Maeso <angel@guzmanmaeso.com>  Mon, 20 Jul 2026 12:00:00 +0200

